  "prompt": "Are there legal frameworks in place to combat money laundering?",
  "response": "Yes, there are several legal frameworks in place to combat money laundering at both national and international levels:\n\n1. International Frameworks:\n- Financial Action Task Force (FATF) recommendations\n- United Nations Convention against Transnational Organized Crime\n- Basel Committee guidelines\n- Egmont Group of Financial Intelligence Units\n\n2. National Legislations:\n- Bank Secrecy Act (United States)\n- Money Laundering Control Act\n- Anti-Money Laundering (AML) regulations\n- Know Your Customer (KYC) requirements\n\n3. Key Compliance Measures:\n- Customer due diligence\n- Transaction monitoring\n- Suspicious activity reporting\n- Enhanced scrutiny of high-risk transactions\n- Client identification procedures\n\n4. Penalties:\n- Substantial financial fines\n- Criminal prosecution\n- Asset seizure\n- Potential imprisonment\n\n5. Regulatory Bodies:\n- Financial intelligence units\n- Central banks\n- Law enforcement agencies\n- Financial regulators\n\nThese frameworks aim to detect, prevent, and prosecute money laundering activities through comprehensive legal and regulatory mechanisms.",
